meta {
  name: GET driving-data SHORT
  type: http
  seq: 48
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/driving-data/SHORT?from=1970-01-01T00:00:00Z&to=2099-12-31T09:59:01Z
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v2.11.2 — short-term trip data for SEAT/CUPRA on the OLA backend.
  Replaces /v1/vehicles/{vin}/trips/shortTerm (404 on PHEV firmwares
  as of #392 heidle78 diag).

  Response carries both per-trip entries (`data[]`) AND lifetime
  aggregate fields at the top level. The integration takes
  entries[0] as the last trip and the aggregate as lifetime totals.

  Response shape (defensive multi-variant):
    {
      "data": [
        {
          "mileage_km" | "mileage": 142,
          "travelTime" | "traveltime": 95,
          "averageSpeed_kmph" | "averageSpeed": 89,
          "averageFuelConsumption": 5.4,
          "averageElectricEngineConsumption": 18.4,
          "tripEndTimestamp" | "timestamp": "..."
        },
        ...
      ],
      "overallMileage_km" | "overallMileage" | "totalMileage": 12345,
      "overallAverageFuelConsumption" | "averageFuelConsumption": 6.1,
      "overallAverageElectricConsumption" | "averageElectricEngineConsumption": 18.9
    }

  Populates last_trip_*, lifetime_*, recent_trips (last 10).
}
